<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState/label> rdfs:comment "\n        User- or program-package-defined identifier for this bead site.\n        This could be used to store primary FF labels in cases where only a\n        secondary specification is required. Otherwise, `alt_labels` are\n        used to document more complex bead identifiers, e.g., bead interactions based\n        on connectivity.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState/label> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState/label> rdfs:label "label" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState/label> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CGBeadState/label> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> rdfs:comment "\n        Tag used to identify the role in the workflow of the same name. Allowed values are 'initial'\n        (not to be confused with the _initial-state approximation_) and 'final'. If 'initial'\n        is used, then `n_excited_electrons` is set to 0 and the degeneracy is set to 1.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> rdfs:label "dscf_state" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> nomad:enumValue "final" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> nomad:enumValue "initial" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/dscf_state> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> rdfs:comment "\n        The electron charge excited for modelling purposes. This is a number between 0 and 1 (Janak state).\n        If `dscf_state` is set to 'initial', then this quantity is set to None (but assumed as excited state).\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> rdfs:label "n_excited_electrons" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> rdfs:range <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/datatype/unit_float%28%29> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.CoreHole/n_excited_electrons> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState/degeneracy> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState/degeneracy> rdfs:comment "\n        The degeneracy of this electronic state level.\n        - For single orbitals: typically 1 (if ml, ms specified) or 2*l+1 (orbital only)\n        - For manifolds: sum of constituent state degeneracies\n        - For symmetry-adapted states: dimension of irreducible representation\n        \n        Can be computed from `spin_orbit_state` or summed from `sub_states`.\n        For correlated systems, represents the many-body state degeneracy.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState/degeneracy> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState/degeneracy> rdfs:label "degeneracy" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.atoms_state.ElectronicState/degeneracy> rdfs:range xsd:integer .
