<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> rdfs:comment "\n        Transformation matrix P relating lattice vectors between this representation and the reference\n        representation. Lattice vectors transform as: (a_alt, b_alt, c_alt) = (a_ref, b_ref, c_ref) @ P^-1.\n        Together with origin_shift, defines how fractional coordinates transform: x_alt = P @ x_ref + p.\n        Both representations use the same implicit Cartesian frame; this matrix only changes how fractional\n        coordinates are expressed relative to different lattice vectors. Commonly used in symmetry analysis\n        to relate input cells to standardized conventional cells (e.g., from [spglib](https://spglib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/definition.html)).\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> rdfs:label "transformation_matrix" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> rdfs:range xsd:double .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.AlternativeRepresentation/transformation_matrix> nomad:shape "[3, 3]"^^xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> rdfs:comment "\n        Formula with the elements ordered by their reduced integer chemical proportion\n        number, and the chemical species replaced by alphabetically ordered letters. The\n        proportion number is omitted if it is 1.\n\n        Examples: H2O becomes A2B and H2O2 becomes AB. The letters are drawn from the English\n        alphabet that may be extended by increasing the number of letters: A, B, ..., Z, Aa, Ab\n        and so on. This definition is in line with the similarly named OPTIMADE definition.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> rdfs:label "anonymous" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/anonymous> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> rdfs:comment "\n        The chemical formula of the system as a string to be descriptive of the computation.\n        It is derived from `elemental_composition` if not specified, with non-reduced integer\n        numbers for the proportions of the elements.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> rdfs:label "descriptive" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/descriptive> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> rdfs:comment "\n        Chemical formula where Carbon is placed first, then Hydrogen, and then all the other\n        elements in alphabetical order. If Carbon is not present, the order is alphabetical.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> rdfs:label "hill" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/hill> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> rdfs:comment "\n        Chemical formula where the elements are ordered using a formal list based on\n        electronegativity as defined in the IUPAC nomenclature of inorganic chemistry (2005):\n\n            - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_inorganic_compounds\n\n        Contains reduced integer chemical proportion numbers where the proportion number\n        is omitted if it is 1.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> rdfs:label "iupac" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> rdfs:range xsd:string .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/iupac> nomad:propertyKind "quantity" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/reduced> rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/reduced> rdfs:comment "\n        Alphabetically sorted chemical formula with reduced integer chemical proportion\n        numbers. The proportion number is omitted if it is 1.\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/reduced> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_system.ChemicalFormula/reduced> rdfs:label "reduced" .
