<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.Pseudopotential/r_core> rdfs:comment "\n        Core radius defining the pseudopotential smoothing region:\n        - For norm-conserving and ultrasoft pseudopotentials: smaller values require higher\n          cutoff energies but provide better transferability and accuracy\n        - For PAW: augmentation sphere radius; PAW's all-electron reconstruction mitigates\n          the traditional hardness/cutoff tradeoff while maintaining accuracy\n        - Useful for detecting overlapping augmentation spheres in small unit cells\n        " .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.Pseudopotential/r_core> rdfs:domain <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.Pseudopotential> .
