<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer/native_tier> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/subsection/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer/basis_set_components> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer> nomad:hasSubSection <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetComponent> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer> nomad:pythonClass "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetContainer> nomad:pythonModule "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> rdfs:comment "TREXIO-style ECP storage for quantum chemistry calculations with Gaussian basis sets.\n\nEffective Core Potentials (ECPs) replace core electrons with analytical potentials\nexpressed as sums of Gaussian functions. This representation is used in quantum chemistry\ncodes (Gaussian, ORCA, Molpro, Q-Chem, NWChem) to reduce computational cost while\nmaintaining accuracy for valence electrons.\n\nStorage format (TREXIO convention):\n  - Per-nucleus arrays: z_core[nucleus], max_ang_mom_plus_1[nucleus]\n  - Flat list of projector items: size ecp_num with nucleus_index, ang_mom, exponent, coefficient, power\n\nNote: This class stores analytical ECPs for Gaussian basis set codes. It does NOT represent\npseudopotentials used in plane-wave DFT codes (PAW, ultrasoft, norm-conserving). For metadata\nabout plane-wave pseudopotentials, see the `Pseudopotential` class in numerical_settings.py." .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> rdfs:label "EffectiveCorePotential" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> rdfs:subClassOf <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.BasisSetComponent> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/ang_mom> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/coefficient> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/ecp_name> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/ecp_num> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/exponent> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/max_ang_mom_plus_1> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/nucleus_index> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/power> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential/z_core> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:pythonClass "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.EffectiveCorePotential> nomad:pythonModule "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.MuffinTinRegion> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.basis_set.MuffinTinRegion> rdfs:comment "Muffin-tin region around atoms, containing the augmented part of the APW basis set.\nThe latter is structured by l-channel. Each channel contains a base (S)(L)APW definition,\nwhich may be extended via local orbitals." .
