<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ExcitedStateMethodology> rdfs:comment "A base section used to define the parameters typical of excited-state calculations. \"ExcitedStateMethodology\"\nmainly refers to methodologies which consider many-body effects as a perturbation of the original\nDFT Hamiltonian. These are: GW, TDDFT, BSE." .
