<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> rdfs:comment "Defines a Hartree-Fock (HF) calculation.\n\nIn HF theory:\n  - RHF  = Restricted Hartree-Fock, for closed-shell systems.\n  - UHF  = Unrestricted Hartree-Fock, allows different orbitals for alpha/beta spin.\n  - ROHF = Restricted Open-Shell Hartree-Fock, a partially restricted approach for\n           open-shell systems.\n\n**References**:\n  - Roothaan, C. C. J. (1951). \"New Developments in Molecular Orbital Theory.\"\n    Rev. Mod. Phys. 23, 69.\n  - Szabo, A., & Ostlund, N. S. (1989). *Modern Quantum Chemistry*. McGraw-Hill.\n  - Jensen, F. (2007). *Introduction to Computational Chemistry*. 2nd ed., Wiley." .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> rdfs:label "HF" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> rdfs:subClassOf <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ModelMethodElectronic> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF/type> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> nomad:pythonClass "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.HF> nomad:pythonModule "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> rdfs:comment "Implicit-solvent or polarizable continuum treatments.\n\nExamples include PCM and its variants (IEF-PCM, CPCM), COSMO, COSMO-RS,\nSMD, GBSA, and Poisson-Boltzmann (PB) models.  The essential parameters\nare the dielectric constant **ε** of the solvent, a description of how\nthe cavity is constructed, and optional surface-charge or\ndispersion terms used by the model.\n\nReferences\n----------\n•  J. Tomasi, B. Mennucci, R. Cammi, *Chem. Rev.* **105**, 2999 (2005) - PCM overview\n•  A. Klamt, *J. Phys. Chem.* **99**, 2224 (1995) - COSMO\n•  A. V. Marenich *et al.*, *J. Chem. Phys. B* **113**, 6378 (2009) - SMD" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> rdfs:label "ImplicitSolvationModel" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> rdfs:subClassOf <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.BaseModelMethod> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/cavity_construction> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/dielectric_constant> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/dielectric_constant_optical> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/is_mixture> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/model> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/refractive_index> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:definesProperty <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/quantity/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel/solvent> .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:pythonClass "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ImplicitSolvationModel> nomad:pythonModule "nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ModelMethod> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ModelMethod> rdfs:comment "A base section for the method-defining choices of a simulation. Store here choices that change\nthe target Hamiltonian, governing equations, ansatz, or physical approximation used by the\nsimulation. Numerical controls for discretization, convergence, basis representations, solver\nexecution, or related implementation details belong in `numerical_settings`.\n\nOptionally, this section can be decomposed in a series of contributions by storing them under\nthe `contributions` quantity." .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ModelMethod> rdfs:label "ModelMethod" .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.ModelMethod> rdfs:subClassOf <https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.model_method.BaseModelMethod> .
