<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.NumericalSettings> rdf:type owl:Class .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.NumericalSettings> rdfs:comment "A base section used to define how a chosen `ModelMethod` is realized numerically in a\nsimulation. These settings capture discretization, convergence, basis or auxiliary\nrepresentations, solver controls, and related evaluation choices.\n\nAs a rule of thumb, changing only `NumericalSettings` should not change the intended model\nsemantics, even though it can change numerical accuracy, stability, or computational cost." .
<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.NumericalSettings> rdfs:label "NumericalSettings" .
